# =============================================================================
# Home SIEM — docker/ ignore rules
# =============================================================================
# Note on scope: Elasticsearch data and certificate material are NOT ignored
# here because they never touch this directory in the first place — both
# live in Docker-managed named volumes (es-data, es-certs, ca-public, certs),
# not in bind-mounted host folders (04-docker-architecture.md, Section 8;
# docker-deployment.md, Section 6). There is deliberately no elasticsearch/
# or certs/ path under docker/ for this file to ignore.
# =============================================================================

# Real environment file — contains host-specific and secret values.
# Only .env.example is version-controlled.
.env

# Exported Elasticsearch snapshots and Compose configuration backups are
# generated artifacts, not source-controlled content
# (docker-deployment.md, Section 13).
backups/*
!backups/.gitkeep

# Exported Docker container logs are generated artifacts, not source
# -controlled content (docker-deployment.md, Section 12).
logs/*
!logs/.gitkeep

# Local Compose overrides and platform scratch files.
docker-compose.override.yml
compose.override.yml
*.local.yml
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
